Package: magrittr.plus
Type: Package
Title: Drop-In Replacement for Magrittr with Advanced Accessors and Replacement
Version: 0.3
Date: 2016-09-19
Authors@R: c(
    person("Christopher", "Brown", , "chris.brown@decisionpatterns.com", c("aut", "cre") ),
    person("Decision Patterns", role = "cph")
    )
Description: This packages provides a monkey patch for 'magrittr' so that
    elements of recursive objects (e.g. lists, data.frames, S3, S4, R6, env,
    etc,) can be accessed using only the pipe '%>%' operator. That is,
    'magrittr.enhanced' looks for the RHS of the pipe *within* the LHS first.
    This enhancement eliminates the need for `extract2`; promotes more concise
    and legible code.
    A replacement method also allows for inline replacement of recursive values:
    'LHS %>% RHS <- newvalue'
